News

Major Ipswich exhibition extended

8th March 2019
The iconic Women 100 art exhibition in Ipswich has been extended by a month, it was announced today (Friday) on International Women’s Day.

100 days to go until Elmer arrives

7th March 2019
It is almost as if we planned it… what good fortune that this year’s World Book Day falls on Thursday 7th March, marking exactly 100 days to go until Elmer’s Big Parade Suffolk goes live.

Support needed for community football event

6th March 2019
The countdown is on to a football-based community event in Ipswich and organisers are on the look-out for support and volunteers from across Suffolk.

Kiss & Tell by touch

1st March 2019
Unscene Suffolk and Ipswich Museum are delivering a series of FREE creative workshops for visually impaired people based around the Christchurch Mansion exhibition “Kiss & Tell”.

Car park closed for two weeks

28th February 2019
The temporary car park next to Stoke Bridge in Ipswich is to close for two weeks to allow public space improvements to continue.
